      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "REGGIO CALABRIA (1) got a long way back over 1230m last time out and never got into the race when beaten a long way. Back to 1100m looks a good move and the barrier gives Tsang options. The claim comes in handy and he can get back to winning ways. PERFECT SISTER (3) resumes today for the Wolfe barn after starting her career with Dan Morton. She'll be fitter for a trial last month before making the move and the booking of Faithfull is a good push for her chances on resumption. INSYDE SUCCESS (2) rarely runs a poor race, ending up in the placings his past three outings, including over this track and trip most recently. Drawn to find the front again for Campbell and the rise in weight indicates this is an easier assignment. Can feature in the finish again. EL FOXIE (4) won't be far away if he can pick up from where he left off. AUTOFOCUS (7) is not out of this on recent form.",
